content.description: Stick clip the high 1st bolt, or warm up on unknown to the left, and clip the first bolt of this climb (on the right) as you lower off. The crux is right of the ledge, and requires a big left handed dead point to the good hold. folks under 5'10' may have more difficulty with this move. After the last bolt, the climbing eases significantly. Chain anchors.
content.location: The 2nd climb on the the left hand side of the main wall. starts on the low flat ledge.
The upper cliff band. You will walk past this climb on your right as you follow the trail from the rim to the base

content.description: Lay back the steep blocky start, and climb the blunt arete with the help of the finger crack on the left.
content.location: just right of the steep corner crack on the left hand side of the main wall.

content.description:
Pitch 1: Climb a dirty-ish 5.8 pitch past 4 bolts to the chain anchors on the ledge beneath the looming steep white face above.

Pitch 2: climb steep 5.10+ face on good holds to the sloper crux after the last bolt.

A climber at the top of pitch 2 can be lowered to the ground by a climber at the top of pitch 1 with a 60M rope.
content.location: Walk along the base for about 10 min.

content.description: The ho-hum climbing to the first anchor changes to classic featured vertical face climbing up high. This route climbs like something in Owens. Great climb if this is near your limit. 2 raps with a 60m rope will get you down.
content.location: the vertical gray face to the right of the overhanging white roofs in the center left of the main wall.

content.description: climb the thin finger crack to a single mid-route bolt, then into the corner on the left. Finish at chains.
content.protection: Pro to 2", with doubles from .2-.4. Plus 1 bolt
content.location: The thin finger crack is splitter, and obvious. On your left above the meadow, and before the taller main part of the wall.

content.description: Thin, cruxy face down low leads to big moves on steeper jugs up high.
content.location: 10' right of the thin finger crack, above the meadow, before the taller part of the main wall

content.description: Climb the flakes past 3 botls to fixed clips on chains
content.location: the first climb on the left hand side of the main wall. It climbs granite like rock and starts off of a low flat ledge.

content.description:
Climb the low angle buttress/slab for to pitches past chain anchors to fixed climbs and the rim. Rap or walk off/top out.

Pitch 1: 10a

Pitch 2: 5.8
content.location: On the left side of the main wall at the top of the talus/boulder field

content.description: Climb the right side of the prominent and strange flake feature.
content.location: Just right of the projecting flake feature that ends just below a ledge.
